      "role": "user",
      "content": "The \"proactive transparency\" approach still uses the word \"lapse,\" and even if we say it's minor, the press is going to dig into why it happened. If they find out a bucket was just left open because someone forgot to toggle a setting, it's going to look incompetent.\n\nIs there a way to frame this that doesn't involve admitting to a mistake or a lapse in security protocol? Something that makes it sound more like a technical anomaly or a planned part of our infrastructure work?",
